node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Elise Gravel on July 13, 2021 tagging @randomhousekids, and @anneschwartzbooks. May be an illustration of text that says 'ELISE GRAVEL with MYKAELL BLAIS PINK, BLUE AND YOU! under the jackex 1ok ford POSTER! QUESTIONS FOR KIDS ABOUT GENDER STEREOTYPES'.

node.text:
Ever since I made my "Boys can be" and "Girls can be" posters, readers asked me to talk about gender stereotypes in a book. With the precious help of Mykaell Blais from ‪@GRISquebec‬, I finally did, and here's the result! Link in latest story to preorder ❤️  •

•  •   #genderstereotypes #kidlit #picturebook #kids #teaching #sexism #illustration #gender

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Elise Gravel on June 24, 2021. May be a cartoon of text that says 'LET'S STOP PUTTING KIDS IN BOXES. ELISE GRAVEL'.

node.text:
Let’s stop putting kids in gendered boxes! Why limit their potential, interests and personalities based on restrictive social norms? Poor kids. Let them be kids.

•

•

I am a writer of socially engaged (and funny) children’s books and comics. node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Elise Gravel on June 22, 2021. May be a cartoon.

node.text:
This is a free printable poster from 2019 that I made for today’s kids but that I wish I had seen when I was a kid. I wish nobody had ever tried to put human beings in specific boxes and decide what they can and cannot like, feel and enjoy. Let kids be kids. ❤️(free printable available in the Boutique section of my website, link in bio)

node.text:
Changing your mind when presented with new information is the smart thing to do. It’s also very difficult for most people. It would be worrisome if scientists were never revising their previous conclusions. 
Would you like this as a free printable?

node.text:
As a mother of two girls, I’ve heard this a lot and I find it scary. Let’s please stop saying it. It normalizes violence against women and teaches girls that aggression from boys is somewhat positive. 

•
